Class MavenTask

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.lukas783.mdt.api.MavenTask

  • public class MavenTask
extends java.lang.Object
    A POJO that defines a task to complete. Contains all the useful information to build a set of processes for building a maven repository
    Author:
    Lucas Carpenter

    • Constructor Detail

      • MavenTask

        private MavenTask(java.util.UUID id,
                  java.lang.String taskName,
                  java.lang.String workingDirectory,
                  java.lang.String copyToDirectory,
                  java.lang.String renameString,
                  boolean copy,
                  boolean rename,
                  boolean cleanTarget,
                  boolean unpackage,
                  boolean doInstall,
                  boolean enabled)
        Constructs a MavenTask object to be used elsewhere.
        Parameters:
        id - A UUID to match the object to components of the application.
        taskName - The readable name to identify the task.
        workingDirectory - The directory to begin the task inside.
        copyToDirectory - The directory to copy the resulting task to.
        renameString - The string to rename the resulting file/directory to
        copy - Whether to copy the result to another location.
        rename - Whether to rename the result to another name.
        cleanTarget - Whether to run the clean argument when building the process.
        unpackage - Whether to unpackage the resulting package.
        doInstall - Whether to run an install goal or a package goal.
        enabled - Whether the task should be executed when processing.
